WEBVTT

00:08.009 --> 00:11.297
Computer:
Auto-retrieval sequence
complete.

00:11.387 --> 00:13.753
Shield levels are zero.

00:13.848 --> 00:16.965
T-3. Prepare to open canopy.

00:18.227 --> 00:22.891
Biomass indicators are
holding steady at 4-0-9.

00:22.982 --> 00:25.769
The pilot still
hasn't responded.

00:25.860 --> 00:27.270
Another failure.

00:27.361 --> 00:29.147
It can't be.

00:29.238 --> 00:33.151
Phase-negative shield
deployment will eliminate the
tissue liquefaction effect.

00:42.793 --> 00:45.170
Tell that to Officer Jedman.

00:45.254 --> 00:47.666
Linfer:
Jedman mustn't have
followed instructions.

00:47.757 --> 00:51.045
If he didn't recalibrate his
phasing prior to exiting
the wormhole...

00:51.135 --> 00:53.592
Don't blame the pilot
for your mistakes.

00:53.679 --> 00:56.136
I made no mistakes.

00:56.224 --> 01:00.593
l have correctly interpreted
the equations from the
neurochip.

01:00.686 --> 01:02.642
Strapa:
Yes, but...

01:02.730 --> 01:05.267
...those equations
are incomplete.

01:05.358 --> 01:06.768
Linfer:
Nonsense.

01:06.859 --> 01:08.770
The neurochip is designed
to locate

01:08.861 --> 01:11.944
all the wormhole knowledge
in John Crichton's brain.

01:12.031 --> 01:14.864
True. However...

01:14.951 --> 01:19.285
I had Coding Section run a
cross analysis on the data
from the neurochip.

01:19.372 --> 01:25.868
They found a hidden region,
strongly encrypted.

01:25.962 --> 01:28.999
Why hasn't it been
deciphered yet?

01:29.090 --> 01:31.172
lt resists analysis.

01:31.259 --> 01:34.251
It may be meaningless, a mere
glitch in the data stream.

01:34.345 --> 01:38.054
Or it could be the one vital
element for wormhole travel.

01:38.140 --> 01:42.133
The one element we lacked is
the correct phase progression

01:42.228 --> 01:44.844
and I'm convinced we
have that now.

01:44.939 --> 01:46.349
Convinced?

01:46.440 --> 01:47.555
Yes.

01:47.650 --> 01:53.065
In fact, I wish to pilot the
next test flight myself.

01:53.155 --> 01:56.283
As your project leader, I cannot
allow you to take the risk!

01:56.367 --> 01:58.198
Oh, permission granted.

02:04.792 --> 02:07.750
Our time grows short.

02:07.837 --> 02:09.418
We have to take risks.

02:15.219 --> 02:17.210
This has to be the key.

02:19.056 --> 02:20.171
Bring me the neurochip.

02:20.266 --> 02:21.221
Strapa:
Sir?

02:21.309 --> 02:23.766
The neurochip. Now.

02:30.735 --> 02:32.020
Scorpius:
Braca.

02:32.111 --> 02:35.069
Summon Nurse Froy and
report to my quarters.

02:35.156 --> 02:36.771
Braca:
Yes, sir.

02:39.118 --> 02:42.485
Socket in place.
Ready to install the neurochip.

02:42.580 --> 02:44.741
Is this idea wise?

02:46.500 --> 02:47.615
No.

02:47.710 --> 02:49.917
But necessary.

02:51.005 --> 02:53.337
(whirring )

02:59.638 --> 03:01.344
( exhales )

03:02.475 --> 03:04.511
(inhales)

03:04.602 --> 03:05.933
John?

03:12.109 --> 03:13.610
( chuckles )

03:14.445 --> 03:17.687
( echoing ):
John?

03:17.782 --> 03:19.898
John, are you here?

03:20.493 --> 03:23.200
Oh. So you are.

03:23.287 --> 03:25.152
Well, this is different.

03:25.247 --> 03:28.410
Scorpy, I must be in Hell.

03:28.501 --> 03:32.460
Tell me, what's the last
thing you remember?

03:32.546 --> 03:34.662
lce planet. Diagnosan.

03:34.757 --> 03:38.591
He was digging around in my
brain trying to pull your
chip out of my...

03:38.677 --> 03:40.884
Aah, N... He screwed up?

03:40.971 --> 03:43.132
I kicked it on the table?
lam in Hell!

03:43.224 --> 03:49.185
No, no, no, no.
The Diagnosan was successful,
and the neurochip was removed.

03:49.271 --> 03:52.763
And John Crichton is
alive and well.

03:52.858 --> 03:55.349
Then what the hell am
I doing here?

03:56.070 --> 03:57.981
Well strictly speaking,

03:58.072 --> 04:00.484
you're not John Crichton.

04:00.574 --> 04:03.407
But for my purposes,

04:03.494 --> 04:05.359
you'll do.

04:10.209 --> 04:12.575
My name is John Crichton...
I'm lost...
an astronaut.

04:12.670 --> 04:16.413
I got shot through
a wormhole...
In some distant part of the universe...

04:16.507 --> 04:18.088
I'm trying to stay alive...

04:18.175 --> 04:20.086
Aboard this ship...
This living ship...

04:20.177 --> 04:22.884
Of escaped prisoners.
My friends.

04:22.972 --> 04:24.428
If you can hear me...
Beware.

04:24.515 --> 04:26.506
lfl make it back...
Will they follow?

04:26.600 --> 04:29.307
If I open the door...
Are you ready?

04:29.395 --> 04:33.855
Earth is unprepared...
Helpless,
for the nightmares I've seen.

04:33.941 --> 04:36.273
Or should I stay...
Protect my home...

04:36.360 --> 04:38.772
Not show them...
You exist...

04:38.863 --> 04:42.572
But then you will never know
the wonders I've seen.

05:12.396 --> 05:15.012
Crichton:
Scorpy, go away. Go home.

05:15.107 --> 05:16.563
I do not even want to hear it.

05:16.650 --> 05:19.187
I'm sick and tired of having
people clomping around
inside my head.

05:19.278 --> 05:20.393
This time, it's different.

05:20.488 --> 05:22.524
We're not in your head at all.
We're in mine.

05:22.615 --> 05:26.107
Your head? Well, do yourself
a favor. Kick the habit
before it starts.

05:26.202 --> 05:28.363
I'm going for some air.
Do not wait up for me.

05:28.454 --> 05:30.285
(disgusted sigh)

05:33.751 --> 05:35.707
There's nowhere to go.

05:39.006 --> 05:40.371
(sighs)

05:45.387 --> 05:47.002
I'll explain.

05:47.097 --> 05:49.839
I put a chip in
Crichton's brain,

05:49.934 --> 05:52.425
to download the wormhole
equations the Ancients
gave him.

05:52.520 --> 05:57.184
Some neural spillover
also took place,

05:57.274 --> 06:00.391
replicating elements of
Crichton's personality
in the chip.

06:00.486 --> 06:03.273
You'll have to accept it.

06:03.364 --> 06:04.319
You are not John.

06:04.406 --> 06:07.364
All right, Scorp.
Then, what am I?

06:07.451 --> 06:10.318
Bootleg? A ghost?
Holodeck Crichton?

06:10.412 --> 06:12.243
A wandering soul that
ain't got no body?

06:12.331 --> 06:17.416
A duplicate of John's psyche,
existing only within the
neurochip.

06:17.836 --> 06:19.451
And now,

06:21.173 --> 06:23.289
within my own mind.

06:24.218 --> 06:25.333
Why?

06:25.427 --> 06:27.463
I need your help.

06:27.555 --> 06:30.342
(laughs)
Man, I'm a...

06:30.432 --> 06:34.050
I'm a voice inside your head.
What do you plan on
using for leverage?

06:34.144 --> 06:36.180
Persuasion.

06:36.272 --> 06:40.140
You know so little of me.
Let's remedy that.

06:40.234 --> 06:42.691
Let's not and say we did.

06:42.778 --> 06:45.736
My earliest memory...
-Oh, God.

06:48.117 --> 06:49.402
...is pain.

06:49.493 --> 06:51.734
( baby crying )

06:57.209 --> 06:58.790
( screaming )

07:04.383 --> 07:06.339
What the hell is that?

07:06.427 --> 07:09.590
My first 12 cycles of life.

07:09.680 --> 07:12.763
That's a little too
much information.
You can keep your memories.

07:12.850 --> 07:15.262
Don't fight it.
You'll only prolong it.

07:15.352 --> 07:17.263
Now watch.

07:23.485 --> 07:26.648
(whimpering)

07:26.739 --> 07:29.572
Tauza:
You will not cry. Sit up.

07:31.201 --> 07:33.283
(grunting in pain)

07:36.915 --> 07:38.325
Sit up.

07:38.417 --> 07:40.123
(grunting)

07:42.921 --> 07:44.081
(gasps )

07:44.173 --> 07:45.709
Faster.

07:49.303 --> 07:50.463
Why can't you sit up?

07:50.554 --> 07:51.919
(raspy voice):
It's hot.

07:52.014 --> 07:54.801
It's at less than
optimum temperature.

07:55.809 --> 07:57.595
I will make it warmer.

07:57.686 --> 08:00.268
(air rushing in)

08:02.858 --> 08:05.099
Do you know why you're here?

08:05.194 --> 08:06.309
'Cause I'm weak.

08:06.403 --> 08:08.564
Why are you weak?

08:08.656 --> 08:11.443
I am partly... Sebacean.

08:11.533 --> 08:13.319
Because?

08:13.410 --> 08:15.492
Father was Sebacean.

08:15.579 --> 08:16.659
And?

08:16.747 --> 08:19.864
Forced my mother to birth me.

08:26.632 --> 08:29.169
(console beeping )

08:32.388 --> 08:34.720
Pilot, the deep space variances
are increasing.

08:34.807 --> 08:36.513
There is a wormhole around
here somewhere.

08:36.600 --> 08:39.137
Why don't we double back
and triangulate?
-Again?

08:39.228 --> 08:42.186
Yes, again. Unless you and Moya
have something you'd
rather be doing?

08:42.272 --> 08:44.308
You wanna park and
take a nap?

08:44.400 --> 08:49.110
No. Moya is actually enjoying
this opportunity for
free flight.

08:49.196 --> 08:53.189
Retracing the last vector now.
-Thank you.

08:53.283 --> 08:59.074
Uh, you know, we've been flying
around aimlessly for nearly
15 solar days, John.

08:59.164 --> 09:01.200
It's not aimless, D'Argo.
There's a wormhole out there.
I can smell it.

09:01.291 --> 09:05.660
Besides, it keeps Moya's mind
off of Talyn and the
Retrieval Squad.

09:05.754 --> 09:07.836
Well, it hasn't stopped me
thinking about them.

09:07.923 --> 09:09.788
Yeah? Well, what do you want
me to do about that?

09:09.883 --> 09:13.046
You're the one who decided we
should stay away and let
them deal with it.

09:13.137 --> 09:15.844
Which suits you perfectly so
you can indulge yourself.

09:15.931 --> 09:17.262
Fine. I'm indulging myself.

09:17.349 --> 09:19.681
Maybe I'm entitled,
once in a while.

09:19.768 --> 09:21.053
Once in a while?

09:21.145 --> 09:24.763
You wanna push this,
Mister Let's Go Find My Son?

09:24.857 --> 09:26.347
Look, it doesn't matter
what I think.

09:26.442 --> 09:31.152
The point is that Chiana
and Jool really need to
get off this ship.

09:31.238 --> 09:34.321
They're driving each other
insane, they are driving
me insane.

09:34.408 --> 09:36.069
So do me a favor.

09:36.160 --> 09:38.526
Indulge them for once.

09:40.539 --> 09:42.245
The girls.

09:42.958 --> 09:44.664
Okay.

09:44.752 --> 09:49.041
If this vector comes up empty,
we'll bag it and go for
some shore leave.

09:50.466 --> 09:51.501
(sighs)

09:51.592 --> 09:53.173
You happy?
-Very happy.

09:53.260 --> 09:55.171
Glad you're happy.

09:55.262 --> 09:59.255
Hey, look, um, sorry
iflsnapped.

10:01.560 --> 10:04.267
You could use some sleep.

10:04.354 --> 10:06.390
Yeah, you're right. Pilot.

10:06.482 --> 10:10.816
Yes, Commander. l'll wake
you the microt Moya
senses anything.

10:10.903 --> 10:12.564
You're the man.

10:15.407 --> 10:18.114
Pilot let him sleep
for 12 arns.

10:18.202 --> 10:20.193
Don't wake him up
no matter what.

10:20.287 --> 10:22.278
Agreed.

10:24.124 --> 10:28.083
The home movies are
fascinating, Scorpy, but
why show them to me?

10:28.170 --> 10:31.879
Patience, and all
will be clear.

10:32.966 --> 10:35.173
The Scarran's name was Tauza.

10:35.260 --> 10:37.672
No one else entered,
nor spoke to me.

10:38.889 --> 10:41.881
With what condition
were you born?

10:41.975 --> 10:43.306
Sebacean heat delirium.

10:43.393 --> 10:46.726
Also known as the Living Death.

10:46.814 --> 10:48.930
Who saved you from it?

10:49.024 --> 10:50.230
Scarrans.

10:50.317 --> 10:52.228
Who specifically?

10:52.319 --> 10:53.149
You.

10:53.237 --> 10:55.979
Are you Scarran or Sebacean?

10:56.073 --> 10:57.188
Scarran.

10:57.282 --> 10:59.534
Then you cannot be weak.

10:59.618 --> 11:02.109
Sebaceans are weak.

11:02.204 --> 11:05.617
You must become strong.

11:07.501 --> 11:09.287
Scorpius:
She did teach me
strength and...

11:09.378 --> 11:12.870
assisted of course by the
usual Scarran incentives,

11:12.965 --> 11:15.581
l was also taught endurance.

11:17.970 --> 11:19.801
Th... thirsty.

11:19.888 --> 11:22.755
Your liquid is here.

11:22.850 --> 11:25.387
But you must come and get it.

11:25.477 --> 11:26.762
Can't...

11:26.854 --> 11:31.063
There are Sebacean impurities
in your physiology.

11:31.149 --> 11:33.185
You must overcome them.

11:33.277 --> 11:35.939
Water... please...

11:40.617 --> 11:41.732
(slurping)

11:44.454 --> 11:46.740
You pathetic infant.

11:46.832 --> 11:51.292
Never use that word
to me again.

11:51.920 --> 11:53.205
( loud thud )

12:00.345 --> 12:02.051
(pained sigh)

12:03.891 --> 12:05.256
(sighs)

12:07.227 --> 12:10.185
A brief respite before
we continue.

12:20.699 --> 12:21.779
A Prowler?

12:21.867 --> 12:23.152
Pilot:
Yes, sending a distress signal.

12:23.243 --> 12:25.074
Pilot, Starburst away
immediately.

